ocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526538\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526538\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juni 28, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104cnw1665702572057.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cnw1665702572057.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/cnw1665702572057.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"cnw1665702572057\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__lfileload_226112\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Copy the contents of a file into a field or variable, ignoring any file redirections in the assignment file.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__topic_d73976e1_d73977e1_d73978e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__p_d73979e1_d73980e1_d73981e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">lfileload</span>{<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/text</span> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">/raw</code> |\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/image</span> | <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/web</span>}\n               <var class=\"keyword varname\">FilePath</var><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">,</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Target</var> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">UnicodeFormat</var> | <var class=\"keyword varname\">CharSet</var>}</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section p\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__section_w1656ab1b7b5_w1657ab1b7_w1658ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__p_d73982e1_d73983e1_d73984e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">lfileload \"/textfiles/text.txt\", TEXTFIELD</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__topic_d48707e1_d48708e1_d48709e1_d48710e1_d48711e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d617816e104\">\n                       Qualifiers</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__d6753e20\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Qualifiers</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__d6753e20__entry__1\">Qualifier</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__d6753e20__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6753e20__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/text</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6753e20__entry__2\">Translates the raw data from\n\t\t\t\t <var class=\"keyword varname\">FilePath</var> to the system character set or the <var class=\"keyword varname\">UnicodeFormat</var>.\n\t\t\t\t This is the default behavior.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6753e20__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/image</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6753e20__entry__2\">Reads the raw data from\n\t\t\t\t <var class=\"keyword varname\">FilePath</var>, assuming that this data is an image. An initial hash character (#) is\n\t\t\t\t added to the data before copying the data to <var class=\"keyword varname\">Target</var>. (The hash character is an\n\t\t\t\t indicator to show that image data follows.) No further conversion is performed on the data. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6753e20__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/raw</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6753e20__entry__2\">Reads the raw data from\n\t\t\t\t <var class=\"keyword varname\">FilePath</var>, except that the data in <var class=\"keyword varname\">FilePath</var> is assumed not to\n\t\t\t\t be an image; an initial hash character (#) is not added. No further conversion is performed on the\n\t\t\t\t data. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6753e20__entry__1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/web</span>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6753e20__entry__2\">When used in components running in the Web\n\t\t\t\t Application Server, it loads files that were uploaded via the browser. The files are in raw format. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__topic_d48717e1_d48718e1_d48719e1_d48720e1_d48721e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d617816e204\">\n                       Parameters</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__d6754e20\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Parameters</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__d6754e20__entry__1\">Parameter</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__d6754e20__entry__2\">Data Type</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__d6754e20__entry__3\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6754e20__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">FilePath</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6754e20__entry__2\">String</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6754e20__entry__3\">Name and path of the file contents to be\n\t\t\t\t copied; maximum 255 bytes. The file can be located in a zip archive. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6754e20__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Target</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6754e20__entry__2\">String</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6754e20__entry__3\">Name of a field, a variable, or a\n\t\t\t\t parameter to receive the data. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6754e20__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">UnicodeFormat</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6754e20__entry__2\">String</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6754e20__entry__3\">Unicode encoding format of the input file.\n                        Valid values are: <code class=\"ph codeph\">UTF-8</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">UTF-16</code>,\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">UTF-16BE</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">UTF-16LE</code>,\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">UTF-32</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">UTF-32BE</code> and\n                           <code class=\"ph codeph\">UTF-32LE</code>. If not specified, the system character set is\n                        used.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6754e20__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">CharSet</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6754e20__entry__2\">String</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__d6754e20__entry__3\">Character set; overrides the value of the\n                        system character set (<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$SYS_CHARSET</span>). For a list of\n                        supported character sets, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tec1665703247413.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tec1665703247413.html\" title=\"Specify the character set used for communication with the operating system and for communication between Uniface and non-Uniface components, if they are not Unicode-based.\">$SYS_CHARSET</a>.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__topic_d48722e1_d48723e1_d48724e1_d48725e1_d48726e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d617816e336\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6851e1_d6852e1_d6853e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 3. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6851e1_d6852e1_d6853e1__entry__1\">\n Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6851e1_d6852e1_d6853e1__entry__2\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6851e1_d6852e1_d6853e1__entry__1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&gt;=0</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6851e1_d6852e1_d6853e1__entry__2\">\n The number of bytes in <var class=\"keyword varname\">Target</var>.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6851e1_d6852e1_d6853e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-1</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6851e1_d6852e1_d6853e1__entry__2\">\n An I/O error occurred while reading <var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6851e1_d6852e1_d6853e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-4</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6851e1_d6852e1_d6853e1__entry__2\">\n Cannot open <var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 4. </span><span class=\"title\">Values commonly returned by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$procerror</span> following\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">fileload</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">lfileload</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\"> Value </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\"> Error constant </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\"> Meaning </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-4</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;UIOSERR_OPEN_FAILURE&gt;\n\t\t\t\t </code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\"> The table or file could not be opened.\n\t\t\t\t The entity is not painted or the corresponding table or file does not exist in the database. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-12</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;UIOSERR_FILE_READ_WRITE&gt;\n\t\t\t\t </code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\"> An error occurred while trying to read or\n\t\t\t\t write to the file. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">-16</code>  through <code class=\"ph codeph\">-30</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;UNETERR_*&gt;</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\"> Errors during network I/O. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-1101 </code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;UPROCERR_FIELD&gt;\n\t\t\t\t </code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\"> An incorrect field name was provided;\n\t\t\t\t either the field name is not valid syntactically or the field is not available in the component.\n\t\t\t\t </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-1113</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;UPROCERR_PARAMETER&gt;</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\"> Parameter name not valid or not defined.\n\t\t\t\t </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-1114 </code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\t\t\t&lt;UPROCERR_LOCAL_VARIABLE&gt;</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\"> Local variable name not valid or not\n\t\t\t\t defined. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-1115 </code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;UPROCERR_COMPONENT_VARIABLE&gt;</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\"> Component variable name not valid or not\n\t\t\t\t found. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-1116</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;UPROCERR_GENERAL_VARIABLE&gt;</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\"> General variable not valid. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__1\" rowspan=\"1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">-1117</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__2\" rowspan=\"1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\t\t\t\t&lt;UPROCERR_GLOBAL_VARIABLE&gt;</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"cnw1665702572057__table_d6854e1_d6855e1_d6856e1__entry__3\" rowspan=\"1\"> Global variable name not valid or not\n\t\t\t\t found. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__topic_d48727e1_d48728e1_d48729e1_d48730e1_d48731e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d617816e643\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__d5916e20\">Allowed in all component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__topic_d48732e1_d48733e1_d48734e1_d48735e1_d48736e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d617816e652\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__p_d74006e1_d74007e1_d74008e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">lfileload</span> statement copies the contents of <var class=\"keyword varname\">FilePath</var> to the specified <var class=\"keyword varname\">Target</var>, ignoring any file indirections in the assignment file.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__p_d74009e1_d74010e1_d74011e1\">If you want to load contents from a file located on a network, use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">fileload</span>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"cnw1665702572057__p_d74012e1_d74013e1_d74014e1\">In other respects, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">lfileload</span> works like <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">fileload</span>. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rxb1665702568451.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rxb1665702568451.html\" title=\"Copy the contents of a file into a field or variable.\">fileload</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qot1665702571691.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>lfiledump</a><p>Copy the contents of the source object to the specified file on the local file system, ignoring file redirections that might occur in the assignment file.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tec1665703247413.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$SYS_CHARSET</a><p>Specify the character set used for communication with the operating system and for communication between Uniface and non-Uniface components, if they are not Unicode-based.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gaz1665702569498.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$FILELOAD_SINGLE_LINE</a><p>Strip end-of-line character from empty input file when fileload or lfileload is used.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526538\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526538\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "lfileload Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juni 28, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Copy the contents of a file into a field or variable, ignoring any file redirections in the assignment file. lfileload { /text | /raw | /image | /web } FilePath , Target { , UnicodeFormat | CharSet } Example: lfileload \"/textfiles/text.txt\", TEXTFIELD Qualifiers Table 1. Qualifiers Qualifier Description /text Translates the raw data from FilePath to the system character set or the UnicodeFormat . This is the default behavior. /image Reads the raw data from FilePath , assuming that this data is an image. An initial hash character (#) is added to the data before copying the data to Target . (The hash character is an indicator to show that image data follows.) No further conversion is performed on the data. /raw Reads the raw data from FilePath , except that the data in FilePath is assumed not to be an image; an initial hash character (#) is not added. No further conversion is performed on the data. /web When used in components running in the Web Application Server, it loads files that were uploaded via the browser. The files are in raw format. Parameters Table 2. Parameters Parameter Data Type Description FilePath String Name and path of the file contents to be copied; maximum 255 bytes. The file can be located in a zip archive. Target String Name of a field, a variable, or a parameter to receive the data. UnicodeFormat String Unicode encoding format of the input file. Valid values are: UTF-8 , UTF-16 , UTF-16BE , UTF-16LE , UTF-32 , UTF-32BE and UTF-32LE . If not specified, the system character set is used. CharSet String Character set; overrides the value of the system character set ( $SYS_CHARSET ). For a list of supported character sets, see $SYS_CHARSET . Return Values Table 3. Values returned in $status Value Meaning >=0 The number of bytes in Target . -1 An I/O error occurred while reading FileName . -4 Cannot open FileName . Table 4. Values commonly returned by $procerror following fileload and lfileload Value Error constant Meaning -4 <UIOSERR_OPEN_FAILURE> The table or file could not be opened. The entity is not painted or the corresponding table or file does not exist in the database. -12 <UIOSERR_FILE_READ_WRITE> An error occurred while trying to read or write to the file. -16 through -30 <UNETERR_*> Errors during network I/O. -1101 <UPROCERR_FIELD> An incorrect field name was provided; either the field name is not valid syntactically or the field is not available in the component. -1113 <UPROCERR_PARAMETER> Parameter name not valid or not defined. -1114 <UPROCERR_LOCAL_VARIABLE> Local variable name not valid or not defined. -1115 <UPROCERR_COMPONENT_VARIABLE> Component variable name not valid or not found. -1116 <UPROCERR_GENERAL_VARIABLE> General variable not valid. -1117 <UPROCERR_GLOBAL_VARIABLE> Global variable name not valid or not found. Use Allowed in all component types. Description The lfileload statement copies the contents of FilePath to the specified Target , ignoring any file indirections in the assignment file. If you want to load contents from a file located on a network, use fileload . In other respects, lfileload works like fileload . For more information, see fileload . Related Links lfiledump Copy the contents of the source object to the specified file on the local file system, ignoring file redirections that might occur in the assignment file. $SYS_CHARSET Specify the character set used for communication with the operating system and for communication between Uniface and non-Uniface components, if they are not Unicode-based. $FILELOAD_SINGLE_LINE Strip end-of-line character from empty input file when fileload or lfileload is used. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}